  <Sequence sap2010:Annotation.AnnotationText="1.Pre-Condition: At least 2 care units have been configured.  User has direct physician order entry permission&#xD;&#xA;NOTE: Daily BSA should be configured on a flowsheet in order to view daily BSA.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;2.Go to the institution editor and go to the misc tab. Change weight type to admission. &#xD;&#xA;ER: No crashes. No errors.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;3.Go to the care unit list and select the care unit used for testing [TESTUNIT].  Select to edit.  Override weight type to be daily weight.  Select OK and store changes to institution editor. &#xD;&#xA;ER: Will behave as expected per spec &lt;E03_101&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;4. Go to pharmacy product editor and enter configuration as defined the following table Table 3 Drug Configurations.  Store all changes. &#xD;&#xA;ER: Will behave as expected per spec tag &lt;E03_104&gt; and &lt;E36_003&gt; and &lt;E36_006&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;5. Open the Standard order dialog&#xD;&#xA;ER: Will function as per spec tage &lt;E17.7_g&gt; and spec tag &lt;E17.12&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;6. Enter multiple standard medication orders for ibuprofen.  Select the PO route and tablet formulation. Some are BSA based dosing and some do not.  Enter doses.  Select OK to store.&#xD;&#xA;ER: Dose/BSA fields are displayed and enabled.  Dose fields are displayed and enabled. No BSA choice field. No calculated dose fields displayed.  Will function as per spec tag &lt;E17.8&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;7. Select to add standard medication orders for acetaminophen elixir (PO).  Enter max values for the dose fields.&#xD;&#xA;ER: Weight related and calc related fields are not displayed.  Limits are based upon general bounds as per spec tag &lt;E17.4_b&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;8. Exclude all patient types except pediatric and navigate to details area.  Enter details and select OK.&#xD;&#xA;ER: Weight related and calc related fields are now displayed and enabled.  No weight drop down field. The dose field is cleared as it is outside the max of 650mg.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;9. Select to add a standard medication order for acetaminophen elixir.  Enter details.  Do not exclude any patient types.  Select OK.&#xD;&#xA;ER: Weight dose fields are not displayed.  Weight list is not displayed.  Limits are based upon adult as per spec tag &lt;E17.4_b&gt; and &lt;E17.4_j&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;10. Add multiple other standard orders for Furosemide and Labetalol. Some have weight-based doses and some do not.  Some have bsa-based doses and some do not. &#xD;&#xA;ER: No errors. No crashes.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;11. Store all changes.&#xD;&#xA;ER: No crashes. No errors reported.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;12. Go to pharmacy categories and select epinephrine.&#xD;&#xA;ER: No errors or crashes.  will function as per spec tag &lt;E19.4&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;13. Select and enter multiple standard drip orders.  Some are weight based dosing.  Some are not.  Store them all.&#xD;&#xA;ER: Both weight based and non-weight based fields are displayed.  Cannot enter both weight based and non-weight based dose fields.  No weight drop down field is shown.   Rate is calculated for those that are not weight based. &#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;14. Add standard drip orders for dopamine.  Store.&#xD;&#xA;ER: Only weight-based fields are displayed as per spec tag &lt;E17.4_m&gt;  Rate is not calculated.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;15. Add standard drip orders for heparin. Store.&#xD;&#xA;Only non-weight based fields are displayed.  Rate is calculated.  Will function as per spec tag &lt;E17.4_n&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;16. Go to flowsheet editor to the adult flowsheets.  Add all newly entered standard orders for drips and medications to the flowsheet configuration.   Store.&#xD;&#xA;ER: No errors. No crashes.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;17. Activate all changes.&#xD;&#xA;ER: No errors reported." DisplayName="_50973_Setup_Weight_BSA_Infusions" sap:VirtualizedContainerService.HintSize="512,1577" sap2010:WorkflowViewState.IdRef="Sequence_1">
